      "title": "\u2139\ufe0f BD Mask Batch Index \u2014 Channel Extraction",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## BD Mask Batch Index\n\nUse **BD_MaskBatchIndex** when you have a batch of masks (e.g. from `BD_SAM3MultiPrompt` `per_prompt_masks`) and need to extract a single mask by index to feed into channel-packing or per-part processing.\n\n```\nBD_SAM3MultiPrompt\n  \u2514\u2500 per_prompt_masks (N,H,W)\n       \u2514\u2500 BD_MaskBatchIndex [index=0] \u2192 mask (1,H,W)\n            \u2514\u2500 BD_PackChannels [R channel]\n```\n\n**index** supports negative values (\u22121 = last mask). Clamped to [0, N\u22121] automatically.\n**invert** flips the mask before output \u2014 useful to punch out a region instead of selecting it.\n\nThis node is the bridge between SAM3's multi-prompt batch output and any single-mask input such as `BD_PackChannels`, `BD_RemoveBackground (external_mask)`, `BD_FillMaskHoles`, etc.\n"
      ]
    },
